k is the precious life-blood of a master-spirit, embalmed and treasured up on purpose to a life beyond life, and as such it must surely be a necessary commodity.\n\n- Penelope Fitzgerald, The Bookshop\n|\nStruggle is a never ending process. Freedom is never really won, you earn it and win it in every generation.\n\n- Coretta\n|\nNot knowing you can't do something, is sometimes all it takes to do it.\n\n- Ally\n|\nIn every moment of our life, we can deactivate the self-destruction command.\n\n- Marino\n|\nFear tends to come from ignorance. Once I knew what the problem was, it was just a problem, nothing to fear.\n\n- Patrick Rothfuss, The Name of the Wind\n|\nSince the beginning of time, spirituality and religion have been called to fill in the gaps that science did not understand.\n\n- Dan Brown, Angels & Demons\n|\nBooks do pretend ...but squeezed in between is even more that is true—without what you may call the lies, the pages would be too light for the truth, you see?\n\n- Matthew Pearl, The Last Dickens\n|\nWhile a rich man cannot have more than 1440 minutes a day, a clever man makes more time by using OPM or Other People's Minutes.-RVM\n\n- RVM"